.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 6.017
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This role describes a file that may be written into the shipped distribution.
.SH "ATTRIBUTES"
.IX Header "ATTRIBUTES"
.SS "name"
.IX Subsection "name"
This is the name of the file to be written out.
.SS "added_by"
.IX Subsection "added_by"
This is a list of strings describing when and why the file was added
to the distribution and when it was updated (its content, filename, or other attributes).  It will
generally be updated by a plugin implementing the
FileMunger role.  Its accessor will return
the list of strings, concatenated with \f(CW\*(Aq; \*(Aq\fR.
.SS "mode"
.IX Subsection "mode"
This is the mode with which the file should be written out.  It's an integer
with the usual \f(CW\*(C`chmod\*(C'\fR semantics.  It defaults to 0644.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS "is_bytes"
.IX Subsection "is_bytes"
Returns true if the \f(CW\*(C`encoding\*(C'\fR is bytes.  When true, accessing
\&\f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR will be an error.
